---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Pavement Maintenance Case Studies | Asphalt Repair Results"
  description="See field results for Shining Road Technology cold mix asphalt, pavement sealcoat, and asphalt additive projects worldwide."
>
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-3">Case Studies</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 mb-12">Real-world results with our pavement maintenance products</p>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <!-- Case 1 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium text-primary bg-blue-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Pavement Sealcoat</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Parking Area Project</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Commercial Parking Lot Black Sealcoat — Southeast Asia</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Project Scale</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">42,000 m²</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Product Used</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">Black pavement sealcoat</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Result</div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-green-600">Deep black finish and fast reopening</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              A commercial property operator in Southeast Asia selected our black pavement sealcoat to restore oxidized asphalt parking areas while improving surface protection against water, UV exposure, and fuel drips.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              The work was completed in staged sections to keep the property open. The finished surface delivered a uniform black appearance, better customer perception, and same-day controlled traffic reopening.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Case 2 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium text-amber-600 bg-amber-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Cold Mix Asphalt</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Airport Maintenance</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Airport Taxiway Emergency Repairs — Middle East</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Project Type</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">Night-time emergency pothole repairs</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Product Used</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">Cold mix asphalt (permanent grade, 0–10 mm)</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Key Metric</div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-green-600">Repairs completed in 4-hour window — 3× faster than hot mix</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              An international airport in the Middle East needed to repair potholes on an active taxiway during a 4-hour nightly closure window. Hot mix was impractical — the nearest plant was 90 minutes away and the minimum order was uneconomical for small patch quantities.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Using our cold mix asphalt stored on-site, the maintenance crew completed all repairs within the closure window, compacted with a small vibratory roller, and reopened to aircraft traffic immediately. Six months later, all patches remained intact with no FOD (foreign object debris) incidents reported.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Case 3 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium text-green-600 bg-green-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Asphalt Additives</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Recycling Project</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">RAP Recycling Mix Design — East Africa</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Scope</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">High-RAP asphalt mix</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Timeline</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">Lab dosage optimization</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Outcome</div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-green-600">Improved binder workability and compaction</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              A regional asphalt producer wanted to increase reclaimed asphalt pavement usage while maintaining compaction quality and crack resistance. Our technical team evaluated the aged binder and recommended a recycling agent dosage range.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              Trial batches showed improved coating and lower stiffness compared with the untreated RAP mix. The producer adopted the additive for selected base and binder-course mixes where RAP economics were most important.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Case 4 -->
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <div class="p-8">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
              <span class="text-xs font-medium text-purple-600 bg-purple-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Color Pavement Sealcoat</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-gray-400">Urban Safety Project</span>
            </div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4">Bike Lane Color Anti-Skid Coating — South America</h2>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Project Scale</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">18 km bike lane network</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Product Used</div>
                <div class="font-semibold">Color pavement sealcoat</div>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-1">Result</div>
                <div class="font-semibold text-green-600">High-visibility color and anti-skid surface</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
              A city transport department needed a bright, skid-resistant surface for bike lanes and intersection conflict zones without removing the existing asphalt.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600">
              The color pavement sealcoat was spray-applied in thin layers with anti-skid aggregate broadcast at key locations. The finished lanes improved visual guidance while keeping construction disruption low.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center mt-12 bg-primary text-white rounded-2xl p-10">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Have a Similar Project?</h3>
        <p class="text-blue-100 mb-6 max-w-md mx-auto">Tell us about your pavement maintenance challenge — we'll recommend the right product and approach.</p>
        <a href="/contact/" class="inline-flex items-center px-8 py-3 bg-white text-primary font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors">
          Contact Our Technical Team
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
